        Joseph W. Truitt
    



Nov 28, 2014












































Buy Now



















































Graveside services: 10:30 a.m. Tuesday, Dec. 2 at  Greenwood Cemetery. Online condolences: www.lewisfuneralhomes.com.MUSCATINE, Iowa — Joseph W. Truitt, 86, of Muscatine passed away on Thursday, Nov. 27, 2014 at Premier Estates in Muscatine. A memorial fund has been established at the funeral home in Joseph’s name. The Geo. M. Wittich-Lewis Home for Funeral and Cremation Services is handling the arrangements for the Truitt family.
Joseph William Truitt was born on Sept. 4, 1928 in Muscatine the son of Joseph H. and Evelyn (Shoemaker) Truitt. Joseph proudly served his country in the United States Army during WWII. On June 21, 1975 he was united in marriage to Marian M. Edgington in Muscatine.Joseph will be deeply missed by his children, Joe Truitt III and wife, Bettie; Cheryl Fisher and husband, George; Roy Nehas and wife, Janelle; Doug Nehas and wife, Denise; Karen Franck and husband, “Butch”; Andy Truitt and wife, Shirley; Randy Truitt and wife, Kim; Joseph Truitt and wife, Julie; Diane Taylor and husband, Craig and Julie Combs and husband, Rick and 27 grandchildren; many great-grandchildren; one great-great-grandchild; five sisters, Betty, Esther, Norma, Bonnie, Theda and Kathy.
Joseph was preceded in death by his parents, wife, one granddaughter, one sister and one brother.


















































